      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "YOTTIE (5) was first up for 11 weeks when he raced parked and worked but fought well for a 2m second at this venue. Usually races well second-up so expect him to be improved and he showed his promise by placing in both the NSW Derby and the Gold Chalice last time in. MAXO MIGHTY (10) has done a great job to come from wide barriers to win his three starts since joining Jason Grimson, the latest at this venue. Tackles a stronger line-up and may need luck from the back row but he is on the up. NYMBAL NZ (1) impressed when he came from the back row to win the Redcliffe Derby in his Australian debut last week. Tackles a couple of handy rivals here but the ace draw gives him every chance to deliver again. BEROCCA BERNIE (4) has ground to make up on Nymbal through his fifth in the Redcliffe Derby but he was racing well prior, winning his lone attempt at this circuit and distance. Include.",
